definition.value: A polymer composed of repeating (S)-2-hydroxypropanoyl units.
A polymer composed of repeating (R)-2-hydroxypropanoyl units.
An acrylic macromolecule composed of repeating 1,7,7-trimethylbicyclo[2.2.1]heptan-2-yl (isobornyl) propanoate units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating lysyl units joined via 1,6-amide linkages.
A macromolecule composed of repeating L-lysyl units joined via 1,6-amide linkages.
A macromolecule composed of repeating D-lysyl units joined via 1,6-amide linkages.
A macromolecule containing metal-eta5-cyclopentadienyl linkages.
A polymetallocene macromolecule composed of repeating bis(eta5-cyclopentadienyl)iron units.
An acrylic macromolecule, composed of repeating trimethyl[2-(isobutanoyloxy)ethyl]azanium chloride units.
A polymer composed of repeating 2-[(2-aminoethyl)amino]acetyl units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating substituted or unsubstituted vinylcyclopentane units.
A polymer composed of repeating 1,3-cyclopentylene vinylene units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 1-ethylimidazole units.
A poly(alkylene oxide) macromolecule, composed of repeating methyleneoxy units.

Any poly(ethylene glycol) derivative composed of PEG-ylated sorbitan [2-(1,2-dihydroxyethyl)tetrahydrofuran-3,4-diol] normally containing a total of 20 oxyethylene groups, with one or more of the terminal hydroxy groups esterified with a fatty acyl group. They are used as emulsifiers and dispersing agents in some pharmaceuticals products and as defoamers and emulsifiers in some foods.
A polymer composed of PEG-ylated sorbitan, where the total number of poly(ethylene glycol) units is 20 (w + x + y + z = 20) and a single terminal is capped by a palmitoyl group.
A polymer composed of PEG-ylated sorbitan, where the total number of poly(ethylene glycol) units is 20 (w + x + y + z = 20) and a single terminal is capped by a dodecanoyl group.
A polymer composed of PEG-ylated sorbitan, where the total number of poly(ethylene glycol) units is 20 (w + x + y + z = 20) and a single terminal is capped by a stearate group.
A polymer composed of PEG-ylated sorbitan, where the total number of poly(ethylene glycol) units is 20 (w + x + y + z = 20) and a single terminal is capped by an oleoyl group.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 9-ethylcarbazole units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating 1-[(4-methylphenyl)methyl]-4-(pyridin-1-ium-4-yl)pyridin-1-ium units.
An acrylic macromolecule, composed of repeating 2-methylpropanoic acid units.
A polymer composed of repeating isopropylbenzene units.
The role played by a molecular entity, such as an atom or free radical, which is involved in chain-propagating reactions.
An imidazole derivative containing benzyl and chloromethyl substituents at positions 1 and 2, respectively.
A palladium coordination entity consisting of palladium(II) bound to two chlorine atoms.
The enoate ester that is the 1,2-bis(methacryloyl) derivative of ethylene glycol.
A hydrate that is the hexahydrate of nickel sulfate.
A compound of iron and sulfate in which the ratio of iron(3+) to sulfate ions is 3:2.
An enoate ester that is the 1-methacryloyl derivative of propane-1,2-diol.
The hexahydrate of chromium(3+) trichloride.
A potassium salt that is the dipotassium salt of dichromic acid.
A glycosylmannose consisting of two D-mannopyranose residues joined via an alpha-(1->6)-linkage.
A macromolecule composed of repeating triethyl({3-[(4-methylthiophen-3-yl)oxy]propyl})azanium chloride units.
A polymer composed of repeating propylbenzene units.
A (1->4)-beta-D-glucan compound formed by methylating cellulose through exposure to NaOH/CH3Cl.
A poly(ethylene glycol) derivative that is poly(ethylene glycol) in which one of the terminal hydroxy groups has been converted into the corresponding methyl ether.
A macromolecule composed of repeating oxybutylene units.
A glycosylmannose consisting of two D-mannopyranose residues joined via an alpha-(1->3)-linkage.
An ethylenediamine dihydrochloride compound having an N-(1-naphthyl) substituent.
A mannotriose consisting of a mannose residue having two further mannose residues attached via alpha-(1->3)- and alpha-(1->6)-linkages.
A C20 polyunsaturated fatty acid having three triple bonds in the 5-, 8- and 11-positions.
D-Xylose in its pyranose form.

A branched pentasaccharide consisting of an D-GlcNAc residue at the reducing end with a beta-D-Xyl(1->2)-beta-D-Man(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc moiety attached via a beta-(1->4)-linkage and a D-Fuc residue attached via an alpha-(1->3)-linkage.
A linear (1->3)-linked mannan polysaccharide derivative substituted at the 2-O-positions by single residues of either xylose or glucuronic acid.

A branched pentasaccharide consisting of a D-GlcNAc residue at the reducing end with an alpha-D-Man-(1->3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1->6)]-beta-D-Man-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcNAc moiety attached via a beta-(1->4) linkage.
The tertiary alcohol arising from addition of water across the C=C double bond of citronellal.
An icosatrienoic acid having three cis- double bonds at positions 11, 14 and 17.
